        <div class="Assignment-Box">
            <h1>Activity 3: Writing for the Web Workshop</h1>
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Read one of the articles below and summarize the main ideas/highlights/conclusions in two or three sentences. This this will go to the beginning and serve as an overview of the rewritten article.</li>
                <li>Read the article again, identify at least two sub-topics, and restructure the article into two or more sections accordingly.</li>
                <li>Work on a subhead for each section.</li>
                <li>Read each section and summarize the main ideas for that section in two or three sentences, this will go to the beginning of each section and serve as a “section overview.”</li>
                <li>Break long paragraphs into shorter ones – one idea, one paragraph; use lists where appropriate; cut out non-essential information and words – keep the rewrite short and concise.</li>
                <li>Post this on the discussion board before next class.</li>
            </ul>  
            <br>
            <h3>Articles</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><a href=”https://hbr.org/2020/06/do-your-employees-know-why-you-believe-in-racial-equity”>Article 1</a></li>
                <li><a href=”https://hbr.org/2021/06/legacy-companies-need-to-become-more-data-driven-fast">Article 2</a>/li>
                <li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/22/opinion/syria-turkey-refugees.html">Article 3</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/28/well/family/raising-a-nontoxic-man.html">Article 4</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2020/2/19/21142728/samsung-foldable-glass-galaxy-z-flip-explained-schott-corning">Article 5</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://hbr.org/2018/07/collaborative-intelligence-humans-and-ai-are-joining-forces">Article 6</a></li>
            </ul>

